Package: baize-kube
Version: 1.0
Architecture: arm64
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Jean Boutros <jean.boutros@example.com>
Depends: podman, curl, systemd, debconf
Standards-Version: 4.7.0
Homepage: https://github.com/jeanboutros/baize-kube
Description: Rootless minikube cluster service for Raspberry Pi
 Provisions a dedicated system user (baize) that owns and runs a rootless
 minikube cluster via Podman at boot using systemd user services with
 lingering. Configures cgroup v2 memory delegation and implements a
 two-group RBAC model: baize-admins (full cluster admin via
 /etc/baize-kube/admin-kubeconfig) and baize-consumers (per-user
 ServiceAccounts provisioned on-demand with baize-kube-add-consumer).
 Includes management scripts for consumer provisioning, deprovisioning,
 listing, and kubeconfig updates.
